      {
        "id": "vwoFXtNV5tm3du5u",
        "title": "Text 1",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<p>You are going to build moth traps to conduct your experiments and answer the warmup questions you designed. The traps will help you capture a sample of the moths in your neighborhood. You&#x27;ll have to be careful to set them out under the conditions you designed for <em>your experiment</em>. When you&#x27;ve collected your moths, you&#x27;ll document the data from your experiment in cards like this. Here&#x27;s a sample of Frieda&#x27;s Moth collection. What kinds of data did she collect? What can you figure out from the data? You should copy this table into your own workspace and play with the data a little. Can you graph it? How would you enhance it or change it? </p>"
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "AZrM3HaDuIAJ6Nz-",
        "content": {
          "type": "DataCard"
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "D3NQiJnAXdypHQz9",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<p><strong>Trap Tutorial Video</strong></p><p>Watch the video showing how to <a href=\"https://drive.google.com/file/d/135oeHF8WYpVd8iXIYk9Zaoyn-rQx7efG/view\">build a moth trap</a> using (mostly) stuff you&#x27;ve already got! You&#x27;ll build these traps, then count and categorize the kinds of insects you trap the next day using the guide below. </p>"
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "oqWpXYiq8oxK16oR",
        "title": "Moth Identification Guide",
